HEADWORD: Ducker
<hw>Duck"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who,
or that which, ducks; a plunger; a diver.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A cringing, servile person; a fawner.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ducking</ent>⟦br⟧
